name: Celebi V

name: Roselia

name: Grookey

name: Scorbunny

name: Scorbunny
flavorText: A warm-up of running around gets fire energy coursing through this Pokemon's body. Once that happens, it's ready to fight at full power.

name: Raboot

flavorText: Its thick and fluffy fur protects it from the cold and enables it to use hotter fire moves.

Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when this Pokemon moves from your Bench to the Active Spot, you may attach up to 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to it.

name: Cinderace

name: Sizzlipede

Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Burned.

name: Krabby

name: Keldeo V

name: Sobble

name: Drizzile

name: Yamper

name: Clobbopus
flavorText: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: Mawile
flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn't very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: This Pokemon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: You may move all Energy from this Pokemon to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Galarian Stunfisk
flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if it is Knocked Out), discard an Energy from the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Pawniard
flavorText: A pack of these Pokemon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.

name: Bisharp
flavorText: Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your Benched Pawniard.

name: Corviknight
flavorText: This Pokemon reigns supreme in the skies of the Galar region. The black luster of its steel body could drive terror into the heart of any foe.
Attack2Text: You may discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, during your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 100 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Cufant
flavorText: If a job requires serious strength, this Pokemon will excel at it. Its copper body tarnishes in the rain, turning a vibrant green color.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Copperajah
flavorText: These Pokemon live in herds. Their trunks have incredible grip strength, strong enough to crush giant rocks into powder.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has 8 or more damage counters on it, this attack does nothing.

name: Zacian V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and attach any number of Metal Energy cards you find there to this Pokemon. Put the other cards into your hand. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Zamazenta V
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon VMAX.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.

name: Snorlax V
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Snorlax VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Hoothoot
flavorText: It begins to hoot at the same time every day. Some Trainers use them in place of clocks.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokemon with 1 of their Benched Pokemon.

name: Noctowl
flavorText: When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. They shuffle that Pokemon and all attached cards into their deck. Then, shuffle this Pokemon and all attached cards into your deck.

name: Minccino
flavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.
Attack1Text: Look at the top card of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Minccino
flavorText: The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.

name: Cinccino
flavorText: Its body secretes oil that this Pokemon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.
Ability1Text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokemon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may switch a card from your hand with the top card of your deck.

name: Drampa
flavorText: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 2 cards of your deck.

name: Rookidee
flavorText: It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokemon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.

name: Corvisquire
flavorText: Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokemon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.
Attack1Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokemon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Wooloo
flavorText: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokemon is surprisingly strong.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Wooloo
flavorText: Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokemon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.

name: Dubwool
flavorText: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Cramorant V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 160 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Dhelmise V
Attack1Text: If any of your Grass Pokemon were Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack during their last turn, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't use Giga Hammer.

name: Torkoal V
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your deck. If that card is a Fire Energy card, this attack does 90 more damage.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Lapras V
Attack1Text: Attach a Water Energy card from your hand to this Pokemon. If you do, switch it with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Put 2 Water Energy attached to this Pokemon into your hand.

name: Morpeko V
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokemon. If you do, switch it with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Wobbuffet V
Attack1Text: Switch all damage counters on this Pokemon with those on your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Indeedee V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from your Active Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Stonjourner V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Sableye V
Attack1Text: Put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Zacian V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and attach any number of Metal Energy cards you find there to this Pokemon. Put the other cards into your hand. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from your opponent's Pokemon VMAX.
Attack1Text: Discard a Special Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon is now Asleep.

Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon. This attack does 160 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Lapras VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Morpeko VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Stonjourner VMAX
Attack1Text: Attach a Fighting Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokemon. If you do, heal 120 damage from that Pokemon.

name: Snorlax VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each of your Benched Pokemon.

Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and attach any number of Metal Energy cards you find there to this Pokemon. Put the other cards into your hand. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.
